INSERT INTO articles (title, created_at, updated_at, body) values ('History of Croatia', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}
{{History of Croatia}}

[[Croatia]] first appeared as a [[duchy]] in the late 8th century and then as a kingdom in the 10th century. From the 12th century it remained a distinct state with its ruler (''''[[ban (title)|ban]]'''') and [[Croatian Parliament|parliament]], but it obeyed the kings and emperors of various neighboring powers, primarily [[Kingdom of Hungary|Hungary]] and [[Habsburg|Austria]]. 

The period from the 15th to the 17th centuries was marked by bitter struggles with the [[Ottoman Empire]]. After being incorporated in [[Yugoslavia]] for most of the 20th century, Croatia regained independence in 1991.

== Prehistoric Croatia ==
{{see also|Prehistoric Croatia|Theories on the origin of Croats|White Croatia}}
The area known today as Croatia today was inhabited throughout the [[prehistoric period]]. Fossils of [[Neanderthals]] dating to the middle [[Paleolithic|Palaeolithic]] period have been unearthed in  northern Croatia, with the most famous and the best presented site in [[Krapina]].')
