INSERT INTO articles (title, created_at, updated_at, body) values ('Chinese input methods for computers', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '{{Table Hanzi}}
''''''Chinese input methods'''''' are methods that allow a computer user to input [[Chinese characters]] with a standard [[ASCII]] keyboard. Most, if not all, Chinese [[input method]]s fall into one of the two categories: phonetic readings or root shapes. Methods under the phonetic category usually are easier to learn but are less efficient, thus result in slower typing speed (because it typically requires user to choose from a list of phonetically similar characters for input); whereas methods under the root shape category allow very precise and speedy input but has a steeper learning curve (because they often require a thorough understanding in character''s strokes and composition) .

Other methods allow users to write characters directly onto touchscreens , such as those found mobile phones and tablet computers.

