The ''''''Canchim breed'''''' is a breed of [[beef cattle]] developed in Central [[Brazil]] by crossing European [[Charolais cattle]] with [[Indo-Brazilian|Indubrazil cattle]] already kept in Brazil where Asian [[Zebu]] type cattle are best suited to the tropical conditions. When compared with Zebu bulls, Canchim bulls produce the same number of calves, but heavier and of superior quality. Compared to European breeds, the Canchim bull produces calves with the same weight but in larger numbers. The fast growing progeny, from crossbred zebu cows with Canchim bulls, can be slaughtered at 18 months old from feedlots after weaning, up to 24 months old from feedlots after grazing and at 30 months from grazing on the range.

